Hi John,
 
My neighbor an old time mechanic looked at the engine and suggested that I
cut the manifold, set each half on the studs and weld it back together. I
know how to tack weld, so if I do that I can have a friend finish the weld
up. Also I put a straight edge across the manifolds. The one that fits
snuggly is perfect. The one I'm having problems with is about 1/8 off.
 
Do you think the cut and weld method is a good on, or should I buy new
manifolds?
 
Bob

